lenders.name: Darla
lenders.loan_because: others have helped us with food, and etc since my husband had been diagnosed with a terminal illness and is on hospice. Its been a blessing to give back to others. I wish we could give more but with no income we can only give back what little we have. Our other two children have rare disorders too. Our son has had brain surgery for a Chiari malformation, and a tethered spinal cord. He also has mitochondrial disorder and type 1 diabetes. Our daughter has a rare congenital bleeding disorder and takes 3 factors for her disorder and platelets when needed. This is why we give back to others in need. Many times people brought us food to feed our family and clothes to clothe us and blankets to keep us warm. I wanted to be able to give back to someone else in need. I, myself am a recent survivor of cancer with recent news of complications from my cancer. I ask for your prayers for our family as we continue to be the best parents and take care of our family, and try to help others as God has helped us.
lenders.occupational_info: I am a caregiver to my family, and home-school my children. Our children have flourished in learning from home. My son will be done a year early and will major into being a history curator. My daughter has come a long way with a learning disability called dyscalcula. She has increased her scores incredibly and works hard. Her last testing scores showed she is now passed her grade level and continues to learn in a new way to overcome her learning disability. I am proud of my children and husband for fighting through even though we have a lot of stress on our own plate. We could not make it through without prayer and knowing the love that God has for us.
